liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: MASSIVE KICK FROM FARRELL! England kick the ball from the 22 and then win it back straight away with a massive shove at the ruck. Farrell gets the ball 46 metres out and smashes a drop kick through the posts - a massive kick to give England a 15-6 lead!
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 53'  ENGLAND NAILS A DROP GOAL!

children.content: England kick the ball from the 22 and then win it back straight away with a massive shove at the ruck.
Farrell gets the ball 46 metres out and smashes a drop kick through the posts - a massive kick to give England a 15-6 lead!

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Was that the perfect half of rugby from England? Probably. The English tacklers fronted up right from the first moment of that game and allowed the gameplan to be executed to perfection. It's a lot of kicking. An awful lot of kicking. But when the ball is slippery and rain is falling, that's not a bad place to be. And England look content with that gameplan - so much so that South Africa are, for now, struggling to impose themselves on the match. Can England maintain that intensity? Can the Boks get back into the contest?
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: England holds narrow lead at half time

children.content: Was that the perfect half of rugby from England?

And England look content with that gameplan - so much so that South Africa are, for now, struggling to impose themselves on the match.
Can England maintain that intensity? Can the Boks get back into the contest?

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Pieter-Steph Du Toit is pinged for obstruction as Jonny May contested another high ball from Farrell against Cheslin Kolbe. Farrell will kick for the posts, a tough kick from 46 metres out on the angle. The England captain nails it! England leads 12-6!
